              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/24028294/" class="">第100页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/victorzhong/" class=" " title="Kapitan #KCRA">Kapitan #KCRA</a>
                (今日归来不晚 天真作少年)
              
                <span class="allstar50" title="力荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="24028294">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">The limit of political emancipation is immediately seen to consist in the fact that the State can cast off a fetter without men really becoming free from it, that the State can become a free State without men becoming free men. </span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-01-20 05:35</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                The limit of political emancipation is immediately seen to consist in the fact that the State can cast off a fetter without men really becoming free from it, that the State can become a free State without men becoming free men. 
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

